BENIN -The Senator Representing Edo South Senatorial District, Senator Matthew Urhoghide on Saturday called on the Leaders of the Oredo Local Government chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to wholeheartedly embrace governor Godwin Obasek’s government. Urhoghide who made the call at a meeting with the local government party leaders in his house on Saturday also sued for peace among members. The senator urged the party faithful to see Obasek’s led government as a PDP government He cited the PDP Constitution under Code of Conduct, Chapter 3, Part 1, 10 (5) and (6) which say ‘No member of the party (PDP) shall publicly make critical comments about the policies of any government elected on the platform of the party. “And ‘No member of the party [PDP] shall align with other parties or groups to undermine the party or any of its elected governments’ respectively,”. Urhoghide described as anti-party, any violations of this section of the party constitution and urged members to close ranks so that the party can be formidable at all times. The meeting ended with everyone present agreeing in a voice vote to work to ensure that the PDP is one in Oredo local government area.